-------------------------------------------------------------------
Spread & Rest: are the three ... function in front of object/const.
-------------------------------------------------------------------
to merge the array with othre data or object properties with other objects.
ex: 
const numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4];
const newNumbers = [...numbers, 5, 6];
console.log(newNumbers);
O/P: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]

Rest:
to convert the multiple args into an array.
Ex:
const filter = (...args)=>{
  return args.filter(arg=> arg===1);
}
console.log(filter(1, 2, 3, 4));
O/P= [1]
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Destructuring
-------------------------------------------------------------------
to store array elements/objects properties into variables.
const numbers = [1,2];
[num1, num2] = numbers;
console.log(num1, num2);

const person = {name:'suhail', age:32};
[name] = person;
console.log(name);
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Create a copy of array, rather then copying the reference.
-------------------------------------------------------------------
const arr = {name:'sam', age:32};
const newArr = arr;
newArr.name = 'newSam';
console.log(arr.name,newArr.name);
